So what happens next?

6
00:00:33,110 --> 00:00:35,030
让他得到公正审判
We give him his trial.

7
00:00:35,110 --> 00:00:37,280
家父曾是一名牧师 家母曾是一名先知
My father was a priest. My mother was an oracle.

8
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:39,870
我从18岁就在太空堡垒上服役
I've served a Battlestar since I was 18 years old.

9
00:00:39,950 --> 00:00:44,370
当你们选我作工会主席的时候 我保证过会让大家有活干
When you elected me union president, I promised I would keep us working.

10
00:00:44,460 --> 00:00:46,830
你们自己必须亲自爬在齿轮  杠杆... 
You must throw your body on the gears and on the levers

11
00:00:46,920 --> 00:00:49,170
机器上来阻止它们运转
and on the machine itself and make it stop!

12
00:00:49,250 --> 00:00:52,090
罢工  罢工  罢工
ALL: Strike! Strike! Strike! Strike!

13
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:53,720
你还在装作我们的生活从未改变
You're pretending like nothing's changed,

14
00:00:53,800 --> 00:00:57,140
和在新卡布里卡之前一样吗?
that our lives are exactly like they were before we went to New Caprica.

15
00:00:57,220 --> 00:00:58,390
可的确已经不同了
But it is different.

16
00:00:58,470 --> 00:01:00,720
恩  我们只是一时的困境罢了
Yeah, I was just going through a little rough patch.

17
00:01:00,810 --> 00:01:04,020
如果是一世呢?
What if rough patches are all we have left?

18
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:13,740
菲戈斯基  波吕克斯 桑切斯
TYROL: Figurski, Pollux, Sanchez,

19
00:01:13,820 --> 00:01:17,240
你们今晚修理所有轻便引擎 所以推掉所有夜生活吧
you're gonna be rehabbing mule engines tonight so don't make after-dinner plans.

20
00:01:17,320 --> 00:01:19,200
把系统下线检测开关设为软件控制
Set and hold SOL check rigged to SEC.

21
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:27,080
我们不是让道格维尔的平民来替我们进行轻便引擎的维修么
 I thought we were subbing out mule maintenance to the civvies in Dogsville?

22
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:29,830
对  可那里的技工不够
Yeah, we don't got enough mechanics down there.

23
00:01:31,590 --> 00:01:32,590
检查流量
Check flow rate.

24
00:01:32,670 --> 00:01:34,920
流量稳定在2-9-0
POLLUX: Flow rate steady at 290.

25
00:01:37,510 --> 00:01:39,390
什么时候能有休息时间啊  轮机长?
Hey, when are we getting some rack around here, Chief?

26
00:01:39,470 --> 00:01:41,010
我已经连续两周站两班了
I'm standing double watches the last two weeks.

27
00:01:41,100 --> 00:01:42,100
我知道  我知道
I know, I know.

28
00:01:42,180 --> 00:01:43,680
还有我的耳朵里还一直嗡嗡响
Plus, I still got the ringing in my ears.

29
00:01:43,770 --> 00:01:46,270
耳朵里嗡嗡响!
MAN:The ringing in the ears!

30
00:01:46,350 --> 00:01:49,850
对不起 我听不到你说什么 我耳朵里嗡嗡响 你说什么?
TYROL: I'm sorry, I can't hear you. I've got ringing. What's that?

31
00:01:49,940 --> 00:01:51,400
伙计们 有意思
POLLUX: Real funny, guys.

32
00:01:54,190 --> 00:01:55,940
燃料指示器坏了
Hey, fuse indicators are out.

33
00:01:56,030 --> 00:01:59,860
机翼油箱开关设为"满油"  关机      好  停止加油 
Set the wing tank switch to fuel. Power off. All right, tank off.

34
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,280
关闭燃料站
That's it. Kill the fueling stations.

35
00:02:02,370 --> 00:02:05,240
拔出输油管   中尉  油已加满 可以起飞了
Pull the hose. Lt., you're tanked up and ready to roll.

36
00:02:05,330 --> 00:02:07,540
收到  轮机长 准备起飞
Roger that, Chief. Ready to roll.

37
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:16,840
洗好的衣服到了 菲戈斯基 波吕克斯 莱夫
Laundry call, Figurski, Pollux, Redford.

38
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:20,300
快拿走你们的破烂 免得我塞到搅拌机里
Grab your crap before I chuck it in the cycler.

39
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:21,720
把内衣叠成我喜欢的样式了吗?
Fold my undies the way I like?

40
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,810
滚   嘴好刁哇 
Frak off. Oh, nice mouth.

41
00:02:23,890 --> 00:02:26,350
你说他们就让军官这样说话吗?
You think they let officers talk like that?

42
00:02:26,430 --> 00:02:29,140
拿勋章的时候  可要把你的态度改一下
You're gonna have to change your ways when you get them wings.

43
00:02:29,230 --> 00:02:31,270
拿不到勋章了
I'm not getting wings.

44
00:02:31,360 --> 00:02:34,520
他们拒绝了我的飞行训练申请
They rejected my application for flight training.

45
00:02:34,610 --> 00:02:37,280
但你在笔试中却拿了第一  面试不错吧?
I thought you aced the written exam. Interview went well?

46
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:41,570
恩  结果是我处于重要位置 我的离开将导致
Yeah, well, it turns out I'm in a critical position and my leaving would cause

47
00:02:41,660 --> 00:02:44,580
严重任务退步
severe mission degradation.

48
00:02:44,660 --> 00:02:47,250
真逊   "重要位置"个屁
That sucks. Critical position, my ass.

49
00:02:47,330 --> 00:02:50,580
他们只是不愿意让乡巴佬坐进驾驶员的预备室
They just don't want knuckle-draggers stinking up the pilot ready room.

50
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:53,840
好了  够了 都闭嘴吧
All right, that's enough. Lock it up! That's enough.

51
00:02:53,920 --> 00:02:56,170
空军队长告诉我  你从飞行训练落榜了
Look, the CAG told me you got bounced from flight training.

52
00:02:56,260 --> 00:02:58,130
我很遗憾  这事不好受
I'm sorry about that. It sucks.

53
00:02:58,220 --> 00:03:01,340
实话说 我们需要你  你是我们最好的航空设备技工
The truth is we need you down here, you're the best avionics specialist we got.

54
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:03,590
她还知道怎么来叠 老爷们的内衣
And she knows how to fold a man's undies.

55
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,220
嗨 哇 哇 你他妈…
Hey! Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa! You frak...

56
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,810
嗨 拜托 够了
Hey, come on! Hey, whoa! That's enough!

57
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:08,850
够了  别打了 你疯了?   我废了你
Enough! Get off! What, are you crazy? I'll take you apart!

58
00:03:08,930 --> 00:03:10,430
少说两句  菲戈斯基
Hey! Shut up, Figurski!

59
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:13,270
看我不收拾你  快回去工作
I'll pop you in the mouth myself. Now get back to work.

60
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,940
过来  过来
Come here! Come here!

61
00:03:15,020 --> 00:03:17,650
松手 听我说
Hey, hey, hey. Listen to me.

62
00:03:17,730 --> 00:03:22,610
你在这里的工作和坐在驾驶舱里同等重要
Look, you do important work down here, just as important as sitting in a cockpit.

63
00:03:24,990 --> 00:03:26,450
谢谢  轮机长
Thanks, Chief.

64
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:30,290
我要去派送一些重要的洗好的衣物了
I'm gonna deliver some more important laundry.

65
00:03:56,150 --> 00:03:59,610
猛禽机升空了 读数正常
Raptor away. Readings nominal.

66
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:09,370
看来一切都不错  设置航线 飞向2-9-6-5-
Everything looks good. Setting course heading 2965...

67
00:04:09,490 --> 00:04:10,870
怎么他妈回事?
What the frak?

68
00:04:10,950 --> 00:04:13,410
熄火了  RCS推进器卡住了 (译注:RCS=反推力控制系统)
It's a flameout! RCS thrusters jammed!

69
00:04:13,540 --> 00:04:16,500
重启 无效
Restart! No go!

70
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:19,340
卡拉狄加  我是斯卡司 二号引擎推进器完全堵塞
Galactica, Skulls. We have an engine thruster stuck in full position!

71
00:04:19,420 --> 00:04:21,510
一号引擎无法启动
Engine one won't start!

72
00:04:24,090 --> 00:04:27,800
二号引擎着火  快爆炸了 到这里来
There's a fire in engine two! It's gonna blow! Get your ass up here!

73
00:04:39,860 --> 00:04:42,490
弹射  弹射  弹射
Eject! Eject! Eject!

74
00:05:35,160 --> 00:05:38,500
我们走运  一打人受伤  无人遇难
You got off lucky. A dozen injuries. No fatalities.

75
00:05:38,580 --> 00:05:40,170
谢谢
Thank you.

76
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:42,815
你应该检查一下托莉的肩膀 
You should've seen Tory's shoulder. 

77
00:05:42,816 --> 00:05:45,380
我都得帮科特尔医生把它复原
I had to help Cottle put it back into alignment.

78
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:49,930
我一直很忙  几乎没机会到船的这端走走
You know, I am so busy, I hardly ever make it down to this end of the ship.

79
00:05:50,010 --> 00:05:52,180
在舱壁修好前 
And now I'm gonna be living here for God knows how long

80
00:05:52,260 --> 00:05:53,850
我还要一直住这里
until they repair the bulkheads.

81
00:05:53,930 --> 00:05:58,190
如果这里的房间太挤 我的另一张床永远欢迎你
If the quarters become cramped, you're always welcome in one of my beds.

82
00:06:01,940 --> 00:06:03,900
一种说话方式而已
In a manner of speaking.

83
00:06:07,490 --> 00:06:09,570
查清猛禽号出什么事了吗?
Do you have any better idea what happened to your Raptor?

84
00:06:09,660 --> 00:06:11,820
还在调查情况
We're still investigating the situation.

85
00:06:11,910 --> 00:06:16,450
不过看来是泰里恩受到了严重的杂质污染
But it seems that the tylium was seriously contaminated with impurities.

86
00:06:16,540 --> 00:06:19,080
很可能是精炼过程中出现的问题
Most likely, it's a problem with the refining process.

87
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:20,370
那里到底怎么回事?
What the hell's going on there?

88
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:22,880
精炼船曾是舰队里最可靠的船只
The refinery used to be the most reliable ship in the fleet.

89
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:26,260
而现在我每天都能收到那边工头发来一堆的信息
Now every day I start with a stack of messages from that chief.

90
00:06:26,380 --> 00:06:28,170
他叫什么名字?  吉诺・范纳
What is his name? Zeno Fenner.

91
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:33,220
范纳?    抱怨工作条件和交货时间
Fenner, complaining about working conditions and deliveries,

92
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:37,890
还有备件和补助  你能相信么
and spare parts and compensation, if you can believe that.

93
00:06:37,980 --> 00:06:43,440
我们在逃命 这家伙却想着加班奖金
We're on the run for our lives and the guy wants to talk about overtime bonuses.

94
00:06:43,520 --> 00:06:47,230
我们对范纳以及他的生产问题已经够宽容了
We've been more than patient with Fenner and his production problems.

95
00:06:48,490 --> 00:06:51,360
给了他两周时间 让他重新投入工作
Two weeks of sitting here, waiting for him to get his act together.

96
00:06:51,450 --> 00:06:56,830
我不知道你怎么想的 但我准备好去找地球了
I don't know about you, but I'm ready to get back on the road to finding Earth.

97
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,790
我看到的是希望的曙光吗?
Is that a hint of hope I hear?

98
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:05,170
怀疑主义者最后还是决定去寻找地球了?
Is the skeptic suddenly decided that we're on the road to Earth, after all?

99
00:07:06,250 --> 00:07:08,130
我怀疑过吗?
Have I ever doubted it?

100
00:07:14,810 --> 00:07:18,640
我手下的人六个月以来连续工作18个小时才换班
I've got people working 18 hour shifts for the past six months.

101
00:07:18,810 --> 00:07:20,640
你们说一个人这样下去能坚持多久?
How long do you think a man can keep that up?

102
00:07:20,730 --> 00:07:26,150
如果赛昂人出现了 我们的燃料足够让全舰队跳跃一次么?
If the Cylons show up, we have enough fuel to jump the entire fleet, what, once?

103
00:07:26,230 --> 00:07:28,030
也许两次
Maybe twice?

104
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:32,030
这留给我可选择的空间太小了
That's a margin that's much too narrow for me.

105
00:07:32,110 --> 00:07:34,570
对于你和你的手下呢?
How about for you and your men?

106
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:37,490
你有异议 自己想办法解决
You have a problem. Fix it.

107
00:07:37,580 --> 00:07:42,710
继续生产燃料 其他事我们稍后再谈 我保证
Just get the gas flowing. And then we'll talk, I promise you that.

108
00:07:42,790 --> 00:07:46,750
"再谈"?  总是稍后
Then we'll talk. It's always later.

109
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:50,170
有意思的是燃料生产了 
You know, it's funny that when the gas flows,

110
00:07:50,260 --> 00:07:52,220
我的电话却没回音
my phone calls don't get returned.

111
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:55,640
可一旦燃料供给中出现了小差错
But the minute there's a glitch in the fuel supply, I've got face time with

112
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:57,970
我就能和总统 上将见面了
the President and the Admiral.

113
00:07:58,180 --> 00:07:59,390
嗯
Hmm...

114
00:07:59,680 --> 00:08:02,890
也许我们还应该再有些小差错
Maybe we should just start having more glitches.

115
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:04,560
这算是威胁么?
Is that a threat?

116
00:08:04,650 --> 00:08:06,400
正如那本书中所写到的一样...
It's like the book says.

117
00:08:07,270 --> 00:08:10,820
"听取民声就不会惧怕民众"
"If you hear the people, you'll never have to fear the people. "

118
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:12,440
你是说"那本书"吗?
Did you say the book?

119
00:08:12,570 --> 00:08:13,570
嗯
Mmm-hmm.

120
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:18,410
守卫 以在战时勒索及干扰重要服务…
Guards, arrest him for extortion and interrupting vital services

121
00:08:18,490 --> 00:08:19,830
拘捕他
during a time of war.

122
00:08:19,910 --> 00:08:22,870
来吧 把他带走  就这样  去吧 把他带出去
Go ahead, take him away. That's it. Go. Out of here. Gone.

123
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:24,580
跟我来  先生
Come with me, sir.

124
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:29,920
这又是哪一出戏?
What the hell was that?

125
00:08:30,010 --> 00:08:32,420
他在引用波塔尔书中的原话
He was quoting from Baltar's book.

126
00:08:32,510 --> 00:08:35,840
他的律师从禁闭室里带出的那些乱七八糟的东西?
The ramblings that his lawyer smuggled out of the brig?

127
00:08:35,930 --> 00:08:39,350
他让人重印后在舰队里分发
He's having it reprinted and passed out among the Fleet

128
00:08:39,430 --> 00:08:43,270
还把书名定为《我的成与败》 盖尤斯・波塔尔著
and he's calling it My Triumphs, My Mistakes, by Gaius Baltar.

129
00:08:44,560 --> 00:08:49,150
我在考虑来一场老套的焚书运动
I am thinking of having a good old-fashioned book-burning.

130
00:08:50,690 --> 00:08:52,480
肉糕好吃吗? 开始喜欢吃肉糕了
Ooh, algae meatloaf, starting to be a favorite.

131
00:08:52,570 --> 00:08:55,950
那不是给你吃的 还记得我们的谈话吗?
It's not for you. Remember our little talk?

132
00:08:57,120 --> 00:08:59,660
今天是我的"作弊日" (译注:节食过程中  一周内唯一可以大吃大喝的日子)
Oh, but today's my cheat day.

133
00:08:59,740 --> 00:09:02,290
前三天都是你的"作弊日"
The last three days have been your cheat day.

134
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:04,620
是吗?
Really?

135
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,170
你昨天移动更灵活的
You were moving better yesterday.

136
00:09:09,790 --> 00:09:11,550
屈身运动就这点用处?
Is that how the bends are supposed to work?

137
00:09:11,630 --> 00:09:15,720
我只是替希里克斯难过 所以有点紧张
I'm just upset about Seelix, so I'm tensing up.

138
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:19,720
他们早就该告诉她舰队里的首要任务是什么
They should've just told her right off the bat what the fleet priorities are.

139
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:22,640
应该告诉她 比起驾驶员来
Should've said that they needed knuckle-draggers

140
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:24,230
他们更需要工人
more than they need pilots.

141
00:09:24,310 --> 00:09:26,310
这不是"舰队首要任务"的问题
It isn't about fleet priorities.

142
00:09:27,190 --> 00:09:30,860
我们不是统治阶级 所以只能干脏活
We're not part of the ruling class, so we're stuck doing the dirty work.

143
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:32,940
"统治阶级"  这词你从哪听到的?
The ruling class? Where'd you get that?

144
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:36,650
我读的书上 波塔尔写的书
Something I read, by Baltar.

145
00:09:39,070 --> 00:09:41,450
这些破书还在舰队里传开了
Those frakking rags making their way around the fleet?

146
00:09:41,530 --> 00:09:44,580
没想到还会有人去看那家伙写的东西
I can't believe that anybody's reading anything written by that guy.

147
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:46,750
我原本也是那么想的 可是…
That's what I thought too, but...

148
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:53,250
你是否想过为何所有驾驶员和军官都来自富有的殖民地?
You ever wonder why all the pilots and the officers come from the rich Colonies,

149
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:56,420
像是卡布里卡  沃钢 或是特诺朗
like Caprica, and Virgon, Tauron?

150
00:09:56,510 --> 00:09:59,430
而所有工人都来自贫穷的殖民地
Well, all the knuckle-draggers come from the poor Colonies,

151
00:09:59,510 --> 00:10:02,680
像是爱诺朗  撒纪特恩  还有杰米纳
like Aerelon and Sagitarron and Gemenon.

152
00:10:03,010 --> 00:10:04,970
甲板手扯蛋而已
